    {
        "desc": "This dimly-lit hall seems to have been made to look as much a tribute to the\nbravery, savagery, and recklessness of the orc tribe as the owners of the place\ncould possibly allow. The walls, the roof, and the floor are crudely cut and\nuneven, obviously carved in imitation of orkish work. Hanging on the walls and\nlying in piles on the floor are armour, swords, hammers, shields, scalps,\nflasks, jewellery, gold, and many other things which, judging by their state,\nmust have been collected by Elrond from the bottom of Bruinen when he ordered\nthe ford of Bruinen to dry up.\n",
